    <Note Caller="1" LanguageCode="en" LastEdited="" LastEditedBy="">
      <References>
        <Reference>06000302000042</Reference>
      </References>
      <Content>In {S:06000302000042} it is possible that the phrase δι ὕδατος, literally ‘through water,’ may mean ‘by means of water.’ This has been interpreted by some as an indirect reference to and a prototype of baptism.</Content>
    </Note>
    <Note Caller="2" LanguageCode="en" LastEdited="" LastEditedBy="">
      <References/>
      <Content>It is possible that διασῴζω is somewhat more emphatic in meaning than σῴζω. It is also possible that in a number of contexts σῴζω and διασῴζω may have the added implication of having rescued such persons from a state of illness.</Content>
    </Note>
